olive oil
2 potato
40 g plant-based butter
2 tbs plant-based milk
1 carrot
1 stalk celery
1 leek
2 clove garlic
1 bag baby broccoli
1 tin cannellini beans
½ sachet Seasoning Blend
1 packet Plant-Based Cream
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Slivered Almonds
1 bag parsley
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the
boil. Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water until easily
pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and
return to the pan.
• Add the plant-based butter and plant-based
milk to potato and season generously with salt.
Mash until smooth.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the
potato unpeeled.

• Meanwhile, preheat grill to high.
• Thinly slice carrot, celery and leek. Finely chop
or crush garlic. Cut baby broccoli into thirds.
• Drain and rinse cannellini beans.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive
oil over high heat. Cook carrot, celery, leek
and baby broccoli, stirring occasionally, until
softened, 6-8 minutes.
• Add cannellini beans, Aussie spice blend,
seasoning blend (see ingredients) and garlic
and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Stir in
plant-based cream and simmer until thickened,
2-3 minutes
• Remove from heat, then stir through baby
spinach leaves until just wilted. Season.

• Transfer bean filling to a baking dish and spread
potato mash over the top with a drizzle of olive
oil.
• Grill pie until lightly golden, 8-10 minutes.

TIP: Drizzling with olive oil helps the topping to crisp
and brown!

• Wash and dry the frying pan, then return to
medium-high heat. Toast slivered almonds,
tossing, until toasted, 3-4 minutes.

• Divide creamy cannellini bean and veggie pie
between plates.
• Sprinkle over toasted almonds and tear over
parsley to serve. Enjoy!